()Role Mining kya hai?
--Role Mining ka matlab hai existing users ke access aur permissions ko analyze karke
roles automatically discover karna. Matlab, manually har ek user ke liye role define karne ki jagah,
system ye dekhta hai ki kaun kaun se permissions ek user ke paas hain aur 
similar permissions wale users ko group karke ek role banata hai.

2️⃣ Types of Role Mining:-
()Manual Role Mining:-Admin manually dekh ke roles define karta hai
Time-consuming aur error-prone

()Automated Role Mining:-
Tools aur algorithms automatically analyze karte hain
Example: SailPoint IIQ me automated role discovery hoti hai

()Hybrid Role Mining:-
Automated suggestions milte hain, admin final approve karta hai.

2️⃣ Example Scenario:-
Users & Permissions Table:-
User	Permissions
Rahul---Read Finance, Write Finance
Priya---Read Finance, Write Finance
Anil----View HR, Edit HR
Riya----View HR, Edit HR

example code:-

import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.Map;
import java.util.HashMap;

class Identity {
    String name;
    List<String> permissions = new ArrayList<String>();

    Identity(String name) {
        this.name = name;
    }

    void addPermission(String perm) {
        permissions.add(perm);
    }
}

class Role {
    String roleName;
    List<String> permissions = new ArrayList<String>();

    Role(String roleName) {
        this.roleName = roleName;
    }
}

public class RoleMiningExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        // Create Users
        Identity rahul = new Identity("Rahul");
        rahul.addPermission("Read Finance");
        rahul.addPermission("Write Finance");

        Identity priya = new Identity("Priya");
        priya.addPermission("Read Finance");
        priya.addPermission("Write Finance");

        Identity anil = new Identity("Anil");
        anil.addPermission("View HR");
        anil.addPermission("Edit HR");

        Identity riya = new Identity("Riya");
        riya.addPermission("View HR");
        riya.addPermission("Edit HR");

        List<Identity> users = new ArrayList<Identity>();
        users.add(rahul);
        users.add(priya);
        users.add(anil);
        users.add(riya);

        // Role Mining
        Map<String, Role> discoveredRoles = new HashMap<String, Role>();

        for (Identity user : users) {

            boolean roleFound = false;

            for (Role role : discoveredRoles.values()) {
                if (role.permissions.equals(user.permissions)) {
                    System.out.println(user.name + " assigned to existing role: " + role.roleName);
                    roleFound = true;
                    break;
                }
            }

            if (!roleFound) {
                String roleName = "Role_" + (discoveredRoles.size() + 1);

                Role newRole = new Role(roleName);
                newRole.permissions.addAll(user.permissions);

                discoveredRoles.put(roleName, newRole);

                System.out.println(user.name + " assigned to new role: " + roleName);
            }
        }

        System.out.println("\nDiscovered Roles:");

        for (String rName : discoveredRoles.keySet()) {
            System.out.println(rName + " -> Permissions: " + discoveredRoles.get(rName).permissions);
        }
    }
}

4️⃣ Output Example:-
Rahul assigned to new role: Role_1
Priya assigned to existing role: Role_1
Anil assigned to new role: Role_2
Riya assigned to existing role: Role_2

Discovered Roles:
Role_1 -> Permissions: [Read Finance, Write Finance]
Role_2 -> Permissions: [View HR, Edit HR]

////////*
()discoveredRoles.values() kya deta hai?
discoveredRoles ek Map hai.
Example:-
Map<String, Role> discoveredRoles = new HashMap<>();
Yahan:-
Key = Role name (String)
Value = Role object

values() kya return karta hai?
values() Map ke saare values ka collection deta hai.
Matlab sirf Role objects milte hain, keys nahi.

Example:-
discoveredRoles.put("Role_1", new Role("Finance Role"));
discoveredRoles.put("Role_2", new Role("HR Role"));

Ab agar likhen:-
discoveredRoles.values();

To result milega:-
[Finance Role Object, HR Role Object]
